KetSDA weekly attendance over time

James R. Milks

06 November 2021

Introduction

Weekly attendance at Kettering SDA Church has fluctuated with time. Here I present the results of an analysis of attendance patterns since 2002.

In-person vs Online

Since 2017, the online audience has increased in size and percentage of the total whereas in-person attendance has declined (mostly due to COVID).

In-person vs Online

In-person vs Online

In-person vs Online

  • February 2019 - February 2020 + In-person attendance averaged 569.28 per week + Online attendance averaged 209.22 per week + Average total weekly attendance was 778.5.
  • Since April 2021 + Total church attendance has averaged 803.55 per week + In-person attendance averaged 424.65 + Online attendance averaged 378.9

In-person attendance is down 144.64 but an increase of 169.69 in online attendance has made up for the loss of in-person attendance.

In-person vs Online

Before the pandemic, an average of 26.92% of our weekly audience came from our online ministry. Since reopening, however, 47.51% of our weekly audience has been online.
